claims:
1. A method for detecting the presence of influenza virus and determining selected subsequences of its hemagglutinin (HA) gene, comprising:
(a) obtaining a sample possibly containing an influenza virus;
(b) obtaining a DNA corresponding to an HA gene in a virus in the sample;
(c) obtaining sequence information for at least three portions of the DNA from step (b) corresponding to subsequences of the HA gene comprising (i) a glycosylation sequon; (ii) a receptor-binding site; and (iii) an HA1/HA2 cleavage site.
